      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:4:1:39:9",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ أَبُو الْحَسَنِ ( عليه السلام ) مَا عَالَ امْرُؤٌ فِي اقْتِصَادٍ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Muhammad, from Ahmad Bin Abu Abdullah, from Muhammad Bin Ali, from Muhammad Bin Al Fuzayl, from Musa Bin Bakr who said, ",
          "‘Abu Al-Hassan<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘A person will not be in poverty (while observing) moderation’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "9. Ali ibn Muhammad has narrated from Ahmad ibn abu ‘Abd Allah from Muhammad ibn Ali from Muhammad ibn al-Fudayl from Musa ibn Bakr who has said the following: “Abu al-Hassan, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, once said, ‘With moderation, one does not suffer poverty.’” "
        ]
      }
